Drought metrics documentation

Load the data

Parquet files let you easily query and summarize the entire dataset

#---- Load data ----#
drt <- open_dataset(datPq)

# Summarize median per variable & gcm
# Rows are cells per variable, gcm, scenario.
# Columns are years
# All scenarios have the same data for the historical period, so just pick one.

tic()
drtSumm0 <- drt %>%
  filter(scenario=='ssp126') %>%
  select(-scenario) %>%
  group_by(variable, gcm) %>%
  summarise(
    across(
      .cols = as.character(1981:2014),
      .fns = ~ median(.x, na.rm = TRUE)
    )
  ) %>% collect
toc()
Execution time: 1.215 sec elapsed
#Convert to long format for further processing
drtSumm <- drtSumm0 %>%
 pivot_longer(cols = as.character(1981:2014), names_to = "year") %>%
  mutate(year=as.numeric(year))
